            <section class="content-section" id="solution">
                <h2>Solutions </h2>                
                <ul>
                <li><strong>Transitioned from static, form-driven layouts to a dynamic, Notion-like interface</strong> — implemented flexible page structures, drag-and-drop modules, inline editing, and collapsible sections to let users manage integrations and data pipelines without leaving context.</li>
                <li><strong>Responsive overhaul</strong> — rebuilt the UI grid and component library to work seamlessly across devices and viewports, ensuring enterprise-grade usability for both ops teams on desktops and analysts on laptops/tablets.</li>
                <li><strong>Button-driven interaction model</strong> — replaced buried settings in menus with clear, discoverable, action-oriented buttons; introduced tooltips, hover states, and micro-animations to make functionality more obvious and reduce onboarding friction.</li>
                <li><strong>Search-centric navigation</strong> — added global and contextual search bars with fuzzy matching, filtering, and keyboard shortcuts, dramatically reducing the time to locate datasets, destinations, and transformation scripts.</li>
                <li><strong>Rich, in-context functionality</strong> — allowed key actions (e.g., enabling/disabling sources, editing transformations, viewing real-time event logs) directly from list views and dashboards, minimizing page reloads and context-switching.</li>
                <li><strong>Design system evolution</strong> — contributed new UI patterns, iconography, and reusable components aligned to our expanded interaction model, ensuring visual consistency and scalability as product complexity grew.</li>
                </ul>
